<br>
At 56 the best solo spot IMO is the Spiroc Warrior spawn in Timerous Deep.<br>
<br>
You can solo here pretty much right to 59 after 58 though its painfully slow since you get a lot of greens.<br>
<br>
This is by far not the best spot for quick exp since it will take even the EQ adict about a month per level but it is seldom camped up.<br>
<br>
I was here from level 53/54 right to 59 in between raids and the few groups I could get in more respected areas for the exp grind.<br>
<br>
These MOBs are called Warriors (2 of them they have a level range of 39-41)) but are infact Shaman with a level 24-28 pet.  They hit for over 100 (100-120ish) and cast some DOTs and Ice based DDs.  They also run at SOW.<br>
<br>
The Spiroc Lightbringer will spawn here as well, this is a level 50 Spiroc Pallidan it has 9k HPs and can heal itself.  Unlike a Necro you will need help taking this one down, I suggest a fear caster thats over 40 and you will need to malosi this MOB.<br>
It usually drops nothing but at times will drop some nice spells (level 51-53).<br>
<br>
While the Brownie spawn will give decent exp, it only does so if you can solo it.  At level 56 it is soloable but its very risky sometimes depending on what spells the brownies use on you.<br>
I would wait until 57 or 58 to camp the brownies.<br>
<br>
It is always better to find a group.  But its a bit impossible at times for folks that wish to play the high end game as a mage.<br>
