<br>
Instead, I prefer to use soloing as a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> foundation</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for grouping.  For example, suppose <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Bunny Woods</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is an under-used zone.  I learn how to solo there, starting at the zone entrances, and moving out as I gain confidence.  I learn to navigate the terrain, identify static camps, find the safe spots to meditate.  I determine which creatures are green <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (a Young Death Bunny)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which I can solo reliably <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (a Death Bunny)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which I can just barely solo <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (a Mature Death Bunny)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which I cannot <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (an Elder Death Bunny)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and which are likely to be fatal even to a full group <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (an Ancient Death Bunny)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I identify the casters <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (a Death Bunny Shaman)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, figure out the resistances and vulnerabilities, and research the purpose of the common and uncommon loots <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (Death Bunny Droppings, used to make rogue poison)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Now that I have mastered the zone, it is time to invite some friends.  I may not be able to teleport, heal, resurrect the dead, or enchant metals, but I am possessed of truly awesome and consistant firepower.  Many friends and guildmates five to fifteen levels below me are usually unable to join on the higher level groups or raids, but they are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> perfect</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for my purpose.<br>
<br>
Consider.  If I can solo <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Death Bunnies</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> consistantly, how much <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> faster</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> will it be with a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> 40th level enchantress</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> at my side?  Let's see, clarity, mezz for the occasionally double pull <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (which will stick after Maliso)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and so on.  It takes less mana to outdamage <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, less time to recover for the next pull, and we <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>both</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> get decent experience.  As the higher level, I get the lion's share of experience, and my partner is getting experience for high blues, yellows, and even reds.  And more spawns killed per hour than soloing.<br>
<br>
Rangers or Druids?  Here is a list of spawns to pull, and could you please buff up <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  Clerics or Shamans?  Meet <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Super Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Necromancer?  Let me get my <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rogue Water Pet.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  The only difficult situation is when your sole partner is a pure-melee type.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> can no longer out taunt them, I can't heal them, and besides, they just <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> hate</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> letting <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> do all the work.<br>
<br>
But of course, my partner has friends near their level, and could they please join us?  Sure.  Pretty soon, we are chewing through <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Death Bunnies</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mature Death Bunnies</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> nearly as fast as they can be pulled, and even <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elder Death Bunnies</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> soon feel our wrath.  Now, the moment I log in, I get <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /tells</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> asking if they can join me, and when not, well, I can just solo for a couple hours.<br>
<br>
So instead of spending an hour <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> LFG</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> just to get into an unreliable group, I instead build my own group in a situation I can control.  It also teaches them the proper awe and respect Mages should be shown.<br>
<br>
Outside of guild raids, I have hardly died in several levels.<br>
<br>
